summary: The contact owns a 2016 Keystone Summerland RV. The contact stated while driving 60 mph, the passenger’s side rear tire experienced a blowout. The contact stated no warning light was illuminated. The vehicle was not taken to a local dealer nor an independent mechanic to be diagnosed. The contact changed the tire and the vehicle was repaired. The contact was relating the failure to NHTSA campaign number: 16V322000 (Tires). The manufacturer had been informed of the failure and informed the contact that the vehicle was not included in the recall. The failure mileage was unknown.
